{"id":14881698,"mediaExerciseId":"958828d4-5e87-438f-9b5c-61d8abcd1bfb","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"19A","chapterTitle":"Determining the Target Cash Balance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":672,"solutions":[{"id":6025888,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to explain what represent upper limit, the lower limit, the target balance and interpreting the Miller-Orr model. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/d9767666cf057bea97fb4d72a3aa6fd0/af8bae141882316eb43911b33a10a34a/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/d9767666cf057bea97fb4d72a3aa6fd0/af8bae141882316eb43911b33a10a34a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The lower limit is the minimum amount of money that a company can have in its account, ​and the upper limit is the maximum allowed balance on the account.\n\n​So, in this case, the minimum amount of money a firm must have in its account is the amount of $L=\\$43,000$, and the largest amount of money that firm can have in  account is $U^*=\\$125,000$.\n\n The company's cash balance fluctuate between the lower limit of $\\$43,000$ and the upper limit of $\\$125,000$. In this case, the opptimal cash balance is amount of $\\$80,000$. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":329,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/d9767666cf057bea97fb4d72a3aa6fd0/994a74d9d7d1e8189c00ca00f6089a8f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":165,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/d9767666cf057bea97fb4d72a3aa6fd0/994a74d9d7d1e8189c00ca00f6089a8f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"When the cash balance reaches the upper limit, the firm\ninvests the amount of $U^* - C^*=\\$45,000$ dollars for the purchase of securities. On the other hand, if the cash balance falls to the lower limit, then the company will sell securities worth $C^*-L=\\$35,000$ and  deposit that amount from the sale to the account. \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":173,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/d9767666cf057bea97fb4d72a3aa6fd0/e0c8875cb2dc69659d7f966114fa2912/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":88,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/d9767666cf057bea97fb4d72a3aa6fd0/e0c8875cb2dc69659d7f966114fa2912/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"01c8b513-ad4e-47f1-b6a5-22bad52dbdda","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881699,"exerciseName":"7","page":672,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"af657c77-5907-44fe-80b5-c48d4d6c0468","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19a-exercises-7-af657c77-5907-44fe-80b5-c48d4d6c0468"},{"id":14881700,"exerciseName":"8","page":672,"hasSolution"